ST. PAUL, MN (AP)- In St. Paul, Minnesota, Jason Zucker, Tyler Graovac each had a goal and an assist in the Wild's 6-1 victory over the Buffalo Sabres. 
Zach Parise, Nino Niederreiter, Zac Dalpe and Thomas Vanek also scored, and Charlie Coyle and Mikko Koivu each had two assists. Devan Dubnyk made 10 saves. 
Tim Schaller scored for Buffalo, and Chad Johnson made 36 saves. 
The Sabres close out the preseason on Friday night against the Columbus Blue Jackets. Read or Share this story: http://on.wgrz.com/1RjiYLk More Stories
